# Autoscaling in Kubernetes

Autoscaling automatically increases or decreases infrastructure resources based on demand.

## Horizontal Scaling

Increase number of pods.

Example

```
2 pods → 5 pods
```

## Vertical Scaling

Increase CPU or memory of a single pod.

Example

```
1 CPU → 4 CPU
```

---

# Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA)

HPA automatically scales pods based on CPU or memory usage.

Example:

```
CPU > 50% → increase pods
CPU < 50% → decrease pods
```

